  <compounddef id="TERMHEIGHT" kind="page">
    <compoundname>TERMHEIGHT</compoundname>
    <title>TERMHEIGHT Function</title>
    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">TERMHEIGHT</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Returns the <bold>height</bold> of the current terminal, measured in <bold>character rows</bold>.</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<sect3 id="TERMHEIGHT_1autotoc_md330">
<title>Examples</title>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>&quot;Terminal<sp/>height<sp/>=<sp/>&quot;;<sp/>TERMHEIGHT</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">REM<sp/>Draw<sp/>a<sp/>border<sp/>along<sp/>the<sp/>bottom<sp/>of<sp/>the<sp/>screen</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">CURSOR<sp/>1,<sp/>TERMHEIGHT</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>STRING$(TERMWIDTH,<sp/>&quot;-&quot;)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">REM<sp/>Centre<sp/>text<sp/>vertically</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">midY<sp/>=<sp/>TERMHEIGHT<sp/>/<sp/>2</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">CURSOR<sp/>1,<sp/>midY</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>&quot;Hello,<sp/>world!&quot;</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
</sect3>
<sect3 id="TERMHEIGHT_1autotoc_md332">
<title>Notes</title>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Value is returned as an integer ≥ 1.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Useful for positioning with <ref refid="CURSOR" kindref="compound">CURSOR</ref>.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Works together with <ref refid="TERMWIDTH" kindref="compound">TERMWIDTH</ref> to adapt output to the current terminal size.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
